<body class="bg-light text-dark">
    <div class="container py-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Kesko Rules</h1>
        <p class="lead">Here are the rules for the Kesko language:</p>

        <!-- Phonology -->
        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Phonology</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>Vowels</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>A, E, I, O, U</li>
                    <li>A = /ah/, E = /eh/, I = /ee/, O = /oh/, U = /uh/</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Consonants</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        B, D, F, G, H, J, K, L, M, N, P, Q, R, S, T, V, W, X,
                        Y, Z
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Syllable Structure</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Every syllable must start with a consonant and end with a vowel.</li>
                    <li>Double vowels fuse into long vowel sounds (e.g., <i>aa</i> = /aː/).</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Pronunciation Rules</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        In spelling, if both ‘i’ and ‘e’ appear together, ‘e’ must follow ‘i’ (e.g., ‘nie’), unless ‘i’
                        is followed by ‘y’ (e.g., ‘ity’).
                    </li>
                    <li>The letter "h" is silent.</li>
                    <li>The letter "j" makes an /<i>h</i>/ sound.</li>
                    <li>
                        The letters "t" and "s" next to each other like "ts"
                        makes the /<i>z</i>/ sound.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Grammar -->
        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
                <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Grammar</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>Nouns</h3>
                    <h5>Plural</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>If a word ends in a vowel → add "-n" (<i>luma</i> → <i>luman</i>).</li>
                        <li>If a word ends in a consonant → add "-en" (<i>torp</i> → <i>torpen</i>).</li>
                        <li>No gender marking for nouns.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Pronouns</h5>
                    <div class="table-responsive">
                        <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
                            <thead class="table-light">
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Pronoun</th>
                                    <th>Singular</th>
                                    <th>Plural</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>I</td>
                                    <td>ke /<i>kee</i>/</td>
                                    <td>kes /<i>kees</i>/</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>You</td>
                                    <td>stu /<i>stoo</i>/</td>
                                    <td>vuo /<i>view</i>/</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>He/She</td>
                                    <td>sko (male), ska (female)</td>
                                    <td>skon</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>

                    <h5>Possessives</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>my = kavo</li>
                        <li>your = tuvo</li>
                        <li>his/her/their = sivo</li>
                        <li>our = kanvo</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Adjectives</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>No change for plural.</li>
                        <li>Placed before nouns (<i>val lum</i> = big house).</li>
                        <li>Comparatives: add "-ra" (<i>valra</i> = bigger).</li>
                        <li>Superlatives: add "-ran" (<i>valran</i> = biggest).</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Word Order</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Default: Verb–Subject–Object (VSO) (<i>Fep ke pan</i> = Eat I bread).</li>
                        <li>Questions: Subject–Verb–Object (SVO) with pitch change or add <b>kae</b> at start.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>Negation</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use <b>noz</b> before the verb (<i>Noz fep ke pan</i> = I do not eat bread).</li>
                    </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Verbs -->
        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header bg-info text-dark">
                <h2 class="h5 mb-0">Verbs</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>Infinitives</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>End in <b>-ek</b>, <b>-ak</b>, or <b>-ok</b>.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Example:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>fapir = to eat</li>
                    <li>radir = to run</li>
                    <li>tsukar = to swim</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Conjugations</h5>

                <!-- Verb Conjugations -->
                <h5 class="pt-1">Past Tense:</h5>
                <div class="table-responsive">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
                        <thead class="table-light">
                            <tr>
                                <td></td>
                                <td>Singular</td>
                                <td>Plural</td>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>First Person</td>
                                <td>-vi (<i>fapvi</i>)</td>
                                <td>-vian (<i>fapvian</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Second Person</td>
                                <td>-te (<i>fapte</i>)</td>
                                <td>-tan (<i>faptan</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Third Person</td>
                                <td>-lo (<i>faplo</i>)</td>
                                <td>-lon (<i>faplon</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h5>Present Tense:</h5>
                <div class="table-responsive">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
                        <thead class="table-light">
                            <tr>
                                <td></td>
                                <td>Singular</td>
                                <td>Plural</td>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>First Person</td>
                                <td>-a (<i>fapa</i>)</td>
                                <td>-an (<i>fapan</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Second Person</td>
                                <td>-e (<i>fape</i>)</td>
                                <td>-en (<i>fapen</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Third Person</td>
                                <td>-i (<i>fapi</i>)</td>
                                <td>-in (<i>fapin</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h5>Future Tense:</h5>
                <div class="table-responsive">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
                        <thead class="table-light">
                            <tr>
                                <td></td>
                                <td>Singular</td>
                                <td>Plural</td>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>First Person</td>
                                <td>-mor (<i>fapmor</i>)</td>
                                <td>-moran (<i>fapmoran</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Second Person</td>
                                <td>-rek (<i>faprek</i>)</td>
                                <td>-rekan (<i>faprekan</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Third Person</td>
                                <td>-tal (<i>faptal</i>)</td>
                                <td>-talan (<i>faptalan</i>)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Questions -->
        <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header bg-secondary text-white">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Questions & Numbers</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>Questions</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Yes/No: add <b>kae</b> at start (<i>Kae stu fape pan?</i> = Do you eat bread?)</li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                    <li>who = kwa</li>
                    <li>what = keo</li>
                    <li>where = lue</li>
                    <li>when = temo</li>
                    <li>why = zru</li>
                    <li>how = yave</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Numbers</h5>
                <div class="table-responsive">
                    <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
                        <thead class="table-light">
                            <tr>
                                <th>Number</th>
                                <th>Word</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>1</td>
                                <td>ena</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>2</td>
                                <td>duo</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>3</td>
                                <td>trun</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>4</td>
                                <td>kvar</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>5</td>
                                <td>fim</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>6</td>
                                <td>sesh</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>7</td>
                                <td>septa</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>8</td>
                                <td>okta</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>9</td>
                                <td>nuen</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>10</td>
                                <td>dekra</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('../templates/scripts') %>
</body>

</html>